Vice President Kamala Harris welcomed Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India to the White House and Washington, D.C. Harris highlighted the importance of the partnership between the United States and India, noting their joint efforts in combating COVID-19 and addressing the climate crisis. She also emphasized the need to defend democratic principles and institutions and strengthen democracies globally. Prime Minister Modi expressed his gratitude for the warm welcome and thanked Harris for the support India received during the COVID-19 pandemic. He acknowledged the natural partnership between India and the United States and expressed confidence that their bilateral relationship would continue to strengthen. Modi also extended an invitation to Harris to visit India.